Builds and installs this project's `ctx-*` tool binaries and summarizer prompts from a sibling CTX tooling repo; must be re-run after copying `template/` and whenever the CTX repo updates, since the Claude Code hook and CLAUDE.md invoke these binaries by their hardcoded `target/debug/` path.

Takes the CTX repo path as `$1`, falling back to `$CTX_REPO` env var, then `../CTX`; validates it by checking for `crates/ctx-context/Cargo.toml` and fails loudly otherwise. Builds five cargo packages (`ctx-context ctx-scan ctx-verify ctx-cage ctx-summarize`) but copies six binaries into `target/debug/` — `ctx-cage`'s package emits two binaries, `ctx-cage` and `ctx-run` — so `PACKAGES` (for `cargo build -p`) and `BINARIES` (for copying) are separate lists that must be kept in sync manually if the tooling repo adds/renames a binary. Also copies `summarizer-leaf.md` and `summarizer-rollup.md` from the CTX repo's `prompts/` into this project's `./prompts/`, because `ctx-scan`/`ctx-summarize` resolve that path relative to cwd (project root) at runtime, not relative to the tooling repo. Everything is copied unconditionally on every run (no staleness check), so this script is the only sync mechanism between the two repos.